Supervised Feature Selection

Hypothesis Testing based feature selection using t-Test

Two classes:

Class  1  with mean  1  variance  21Class  2  with mean  2  variance  22Class  1  with mean  1  variance  12Class  2  with mean  2  variance  22

Assumption: 21=22=212=22=2

Hypothesis design for feature selection in classification problem:

1 (Difference between class means is non-zero): 0 (Difference between class means is zero): 12012=0H1 (Difference between class means is non-zero): 120H0 (Difference between class means is zero): 12=0

Feature with higher difference between class means has greater class separability, hence better feature.

Test Statistic

=()(12)2(1)(1)q=(xy)(12)s2N

where

=1=1, are samples values of the feature in class 1=1=1, are samples values of the feature in class 22=122(=1()2+=1()2)class-wise sample variance.x=1Ni=1Nxi,xi are samples values of the feature in class 1y=1Ni=1Nyi,yi are samples values of the feature in class 2s2=12N2(i=1N(xix)2+i=1N(yiy)2)class-wise sample variance.

According to null-hypothesis 0H0, 12=012=0

q follows t-distributution with 222N2 degrees of freedom.

For Feature 1:

In [2]:
f=X[,1]
fw1=f[1:N]
fw2=f[(N+1):(2*N)]
xbar=mean(fw1)
ybar=mean(fw2)
s=sqrt(sum((fw1-xbar)^2)+sum((fw2-ybar)^2)/(2*N-2))
q=(xbar-ybar)/(s*sqrt(2/N))
cat("\n xbar=",xbar," ybar=",ybar)
cat("\n\n Test statistic q= ",q)
cat("\n q follows t- distribution with ",2*N-2," degrees of freedom")

 xbar= 4.949148  ybar= 15.03573

 Test statistic q=  -7.19591
 q follows t- distribution with  398  degrees of freedom

Compute p value

If p-value < 0.05: Feature has signficant difference between the class means

If p-value 0.05: Difference between class means along the feature is not significant

In [3]:

cat("\n p-value for hypothesis test on Feature 1= ",p.val)
alpha=0.05
if(p.val< alpha){
    cat("\n Feature is relevant")  
}else     
    cat("\n Feature  is not relevant, lacks class separability")

In [6]:
d=ncol(X)
q.val=rep(0,d)
for(i in 1:d)
{
    f=X[,i]
    fw1=f[1:N]
    fw2=f[(N+1):(2*N)]
    xbar=mean(fw1)
    ybar=mean(fw2)
    s=sqrt(sum((fw1-xbar)^2)+sum((fw2-ybar)^2)/(2*N-2))
    q=(xbar-ybar)/(s*sqrt(2/N))
    p.val=pt(q,2*N-2)
    cat("\n\n Test statistic q for Feature ",i," = ",q,"p-value=",p.val)
    q.val[i]=q
}
ord=sort(abs(q.val),decreasing=TRUE,index.return=TRUE)$ix
cat("\n\n Ordering of features based on t-Test=",ord)

In [8]:
nclass=length(unique(class))
FDR=rep(0,ncol(X))
for(d in 1:ncol(X))
{
    FDRd=0
    f=X[,d]
     for(i in 1:nclass)
     {
         for(j in 1:nclass)
         {
            if(i!=j)
            {
                fi=f[which(class==i)]
                fj=f[which(class==j)]
                FDRd=FDRd+((mean(fi)-mean(fj))^2)/(var(fi)+var(fj))
            }
            
         } 
     }
    cat("\n FDR for Feature ",d," = ",FDRd)
    FDR[d]=FDRd
}
ord=sort(abs(FDR),decreasing=TRUE,index.return=TRUE)$ix
cat("\n\n Ordering of features based on FDR: \n",paste0(colnames(X)[ord],collapse=", "))

Class-wise prior probability:

()P(i)NiN
  Ni number of samples in class i out of a total of N samples.

Class specific covariance matrix:

=[()()]i=E[(xi)(xi)T]

Global mean vector:

0==1()0=i=1MP(i)i

In [10]:
N=nrow(X)
nclass=length(unique(class))
mu0<-colMeans(X)
S<-list()
Mu<-list()
P<-list()
for(i in 1:nclass)
{
    wi=X[which(class==i),]
    Ni=nrow(wi)
    P[[i]]<-Ni/N
    Mu[[i]]<-colMeans(wi)
    S[[i]]<-cov(wi)
    cat("\n\n Class ",i,": ")
    cat("\n Prior P: ",P[[i]])
    cat("\n Mean Mu: ",Mu[[i]])
    cat("\n Covariance Matrix: \n")
    print(S[[i]])
}

Within-class scatter matrix

==1()(3)(3)Sw=i=1MP(i)i

Between-class scatter matrix

==1()(0)(0)(4)(4)Sb=i=1MP(i)(i0)(i0)T

Mixture scatter matrix

=[(0)(0)]=+(5)(5)Sm=E[(x0)(x0)T]=Sw+Sb
In [11]:
Sw=0
Sb=0
for(i in 1:nclass)
{
    mui0=Mu[[i]]-mu0
    Sw=Sw+ P[[i]]*S[[i]]
    Sb=Sb+ P[[i]]*outer(mui0,mui0)
}
Sm=Sw+Sb
cat("\n\n Within-class scatter matrix: \n")
print(Sw)
cat("\n\n Between-class scatter matrix: \n")
print(Sb)
cat("\n\n Mixture scatter matrix: \n")
print(Sm)

Class separability measures

1={}{}(5)(5)J1=trace{Sm}trace{Sw}
2=||||=|1|(6)(6)J2=|Sm||Sw|=|Sw1Sm|
3={1}(7)(7)J3=trace{Sw1Sm}

|||A| denotes determinant of matrix A.

J3=sum(diag(solve(Sw)%*%Sm))
